# Okta Multi-Branded Login Pages - Environment Setup

Last Modified: 4/16/2018 by Sami

1. 1.Create a Custom Authorization Server

Okta allows you to create custom OAuth 2.0 authorization servers. Create a new custom authorization server for this application.

| 1 | Go to Security  API  Authorization Servers Click on &quot;Add authorization server&quot; button
 ![](data:image/*;base64,)


 |
| --- | --- |
| 2 | Provide below information and click on Save button. Name: Franchisor Org AuthAudience: [https://franchisor.org.com](https://franchisor.org.com)Description: Authorization server for franchisors  |
| 3 | It will add a custom authorization server.
 ![](data:image/*;base64,)


 |
|   | Access Policies: By default, there is no access policies. We will add access policies for our sample application later.   |

1. 2.Create Identity Providers for each brand

Okta allows you to create Identity Providers to manage federations with external Identity Providers (IdP). Each identity provider (IdP) requires some setup. For this application, we will create an Identity Provider for each branded login page.

Go to Security  API  Identity Providers

Click on &quot;Add Identity Provider&quot; button

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1.
  1. 2.1Create Identity Provider for Green Brand Login Page

| 1. | Click on &quot;Add Identity Provider&quot; button |
| --- | --- |
| 2. | Select &quot;Add SAML 2.0 IdP&quot;
 ![](data:image/*;base64,)


 |
| 3. | Name: Green Brand Login PageIdP Username: idpuser.subjectNameIdFilter: UncheckedMatch against: Okta UsernameIf No match is found: Redirect to Okta Sign-in Page **SAML Protocol Settings:** IdP Issuer URI: Green branded Login Page URI. For Example:          [https://login.greenbrand.com](https://login.greenbrand.com) IdP Single Sign-on URI:Green branded Login Page URI. For Example: [https://login.greenbrand.com](https://login.greenbrand.com)   Request Binding: HTTP POSTRequest Signature: UncheckedRest of the fields : Default Values

1. 3.Enabling CORS (Trusted Origins)

In Okta, CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) allows JavaScript hosted on your websites to make an XHR to the Okta API with the Okta session cookie. Every website origin must be explicitly permitted via the administrator UI for CORS. You have to enable CORS for the Branded Login pages

Go to Security  API  Trusted Orgins

| 1. | Add Green Brand Login CORS Click on Add Origin Name: Green Brand LoginOrigin URL: [https://login.greenbrand.com](https://login.greenbrand.com)Type: CORS [Checked]Redirect [Unchecked] Click on Save button
 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)


 |
| --- | --- |
| 2. | Add Blue Brand Login CORS Click on Add Origin Name: Blue Brand LoginOrigin URL: [https://login.bluebrand.com](https://login.bluebrand.com)Type: CORS [Checked]Redirect [Unchecked] Click on Save button
 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)
